Purchasing operations improve when teams follow a consistent reporting rhythm.

## Suggested cadence

- Daily view: urgent pending items and exceptions
- Weekly view: approval flow, supplier delays, and workload
- Monthly view: trend analysis and process improvement priorities

## Key indicators

- Open purchase orders by stage
- Average approval timeline
- Supplier response performance
- Rework and correction rate

A stable reporting rhythm strengthens accountability and supports continuous improvement in procurement workflows.
